    "response": "To compute the **sample variance** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{-22, 22, 11, -19, 8, 7\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the sample mean ($\\bar{x}$)\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{-22 + 22 + 11 - 19 + 8 + 7}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{1}{6} = 0.1667\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared deviations from the mean\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(-22 - 0.1667)^2 &= (-22.1667)^2 \\approx 491.33 \\\\\n(22 - 0.1667)^2 &= (21.8333)^2 \\approx 476.44 \\\\\n(11 - 0.1667)^2 &= (10.8333)^2 \\approx 117.37 \\\\\n(-19 - 0.1667)^2 &= (-19.1667)^2 \\approx 367.29 \\\\\n(8 - 0.1667)^2 &= (7.8333)^2 \\approx 61.35 \\\\\n(7 - 0.1667)^2 &= (6.8333)^2 \\approx 46.68 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared deviations\n\n$$\n\\text{Sum of squares} = 491.33 + 476.44 + 117.37 + 367.29 + 61.35 + 46.68 \\approx 1453.36\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Divide by $n - 1$ (sample variance formula)\n\n$$\ns^2 = \\frac{1453.36}{6 - 1} = \\frac{1453.36}{5} = 290.67\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Final Answer:\n\n$$\n\\boxed{290.67}\n$$"
